```py
SELECT
  date,
  customer,
  order_amount, 
  SUM(order_amount) OVER(PARTITION BY customer) AS total_order_amount
FROM orders
ORDER BY date
```

```py
WITH my_order_table AS (
  SELECT
    date,
    customer,
    order_amount, 
    SUM(order_amount) OVER(PARTITION BY customer) AS total_order_amount
  FROM orders
)

SELECT
  *
FROM my_order_table
WHERE total_order_amount > 5000
ORDER BY date
```

```py
SELECT
  *
FROM 
    (SELECT
      date,
      customer,
      order_amount, 
      SUM(order_amount) OVER(PARTITION BY customer) AS total_order_amount
    FROM orders) AS A

WHERE A.total_order_amount > 5000
ORDER BY A.date
```

```py
SELECT
  date,
  customer,
  order_amount, 
  SUM(order_amount) OVER(PARTITION BY customer) AS total_order_amount
FROM orders
QUALIFY total_order_amount > 5000
```

```py
SELECT
  date,
  customer,
  order_amount, 
FROM orders
QUALIFY SUM(order_amount) OVER(PARTITION BY customer) > 5000
```

```py
SELECT
  Timestamp,
  Product,
  Sale_value,
  ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY Product ORDER BY Timestamp ASC) as row_num
FROM sales
ORDER BY Product, row_num
```

```py
SELECT
  Timestamp,
  Product,
  Sale_value,
  ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY Product ORDER BY Timestamp ASC) as row_num
FROM sales
QUALIFY row_num = 1
ORDER BY Product
```
